DataElement.preferredName: Pulmonary Function Test Forced Expiratory Flow at 25-75 Percent Measurement Lab Percentage Value
DataElement.preferredDefinition: The value as a percentage of 100 related to a broad range of tests that are performed to assess how well lungs inhale and exhale air and how efficiently they transfer oxygen into the blood, specifically the mean forced expiratory flow rate at 25-75% of the forced vital capacity.
